JD 12:

Key Responsibilities

Strategic Sourcing & Procurement:

- Lead procurement for key ingredients: whey protein concentrates/isolates, cocoa powder/butter, almonds, cashews, peanuts, dates, and other nutrition-grade ingredients.

- Source primary & secondary packaging material - laminates, bottles, caps, cartons, labels, pouches, and sustainable packaging formats.

- Build and execute sourcing strategies aligned with production, NPD, and business growth.

Vendor Development & Management:

- Identify, qualify, and onboard reliable suppliers across domestic and global markets.

- Develop alternate vendors to mitigate supply risk and ensure uninterrupted material flow.

- Conduct regular audits, quality checks, and performance assessments with QA & manufacturing teams.

Cost Management & Negotiation:

- Drive cost reduction initiatives without compromising on product quality or safety.

- Negotiate contracts, pricing terms, MOQs, payment terms, and long-term agreements.

- Track commodity pricing trends (dairy proteins, cocoa, nuts, etc.) and plan procurement accordingly.

Inventory, Planning & Operations:

- Work with production and planning teams to maintain optimal inventory levels.

- Ensure timely availability of materials as per production schedules.

- Monitor lead times, logistics, import timelines, and customs processes if sourcing internationally.

Quality, Compliance & Documentation

- Ensure all ingredients and packaging materials meet internal quality standards and regulatory requirements.

- Maintain procurement documentation, supplier agreements, specifications, and traceability records.

- Work closely with R&D on new materials, reformulations, and packaging innovations.

