JD 13:

Key Responsibilities

A. Category Expansion & Brand Partnerships
Develop and scale the Beverages category portfolio for B2B Quick Commerce.
Build a channel-agnostic assortment strategy tailored to kiranas, HoReCa, and commercial buyers.
Drive AOV > INR 10,000 and increase lines per order through optimized assortment and pack size strategy.
Partner with beverage brands to onboard new SKUs, activate demand drivers, and expand distribution into new pockets.
Focus on introducing non-KVI SKUs and new-age beverage segments (functional drinks, premium hydration, health beverages).

B. Drive Long-Term GMV & Profitability
Own and deliver 3–5 year GMV and profit targets for the beverages vertical.
Lead annual and monthly S&OP planning for category & brand performance.
Manage monthly brand-wise P&L, targeting CM1 > 3% through strategic assortment, commercial optimization, and better buying.
Improve product mix, procurement terms, and minimize losses from expiry/slow-moving SKUs.

C. Supplier & Inventory Leadership
Build long-term commercial partnerships with national, regional, and D2C beverage brands.
Maintain negative working capital through optimized credit terms and inventory planning.
Operate with 3-day inventory levels at each micro-fulfillment center.
Maintain fill rates > 100% for KVI SKUs and >90% for non-KVI items.

D. Customer Experience & Retention
Craft and execute customer acquisition and retention strategy for beverages buyers.
Achieve weekly customer retention > 90% and drive >3 repeat orders/customer/day.
Ensure assortment meets evolving demand trends — from mainstream beverages to premium & functional categories.
Incorporate customer feedback & insights into product planning and pricing.

E. Cross-Functional Collaboration
Build quarterly category activation calendar with brand-co funded marketing plans.
Collaborate with Sales & Marketing to drive category visibility, sampling, and pricing plays.
Ensure best-in-class product availability, discoverability, and display strategy.

