JD 44:

Roles & Responsibilities

Lead sourcing and supplier evaluation activities across assigned FMCG categories, collaborating with cross-functional stakeholders to develop data-driven sourcing recommendations and present outcomes to leadership.

Own commercial negotiations and contract lifecycle management, partnering with Legal and Finance to negotiate pricing, rebates, payment terms, service levels, and contract renewals.

Conduct commodity market analysis (raw materials, packaging, agri-inputs, chemicals, oils, paper, etc.) and implement risk mitigation strategies to manage price volatility, supply disruptions, and continuity risks.

Support category planning and inventory management, aligning demand forecasts, stock levels, and replenishment plans with sales trends, seasonality, and promotional cycles.

Monitor and drive supplier performance management through KPIs including cost competitiveness, quality, OTIF, service levels, compliance, and sustainability standards.

Ensure full regulatory, ethical, and supplier compliance, adhering to company policies, audit requirements, and industry standards.

Perform cost and TCO analysis to identify savings and value-creation opportunities through cost optimization, value engineering, and process improvements.

Partner closely with Marketing, Supply Chain, Operations, Quality, Finance, and Planning teams to support category strategies, product launches, and business growth initiatives.

Prepare and present procurement and category performance reports, including savings tracking, supplier scorecards, risk assessments, and executive dashboards.

Contribute to continuous improvement initiatives by enhancing sourcing processes, tools, templates, and governance frameworks across the procurement function.
